\frac{x^2+10x+21}{x^2+4x-21}&=0\\
\Rightarrow \hspace{0.1cm} x^2+10x+21&=0
\end{align*}
Now, factor the quadratic expression. \begin{align*}
x^2+10x+21&=0\\
\Rightarrow \hspace{0.2cm}(x+3)(x+7)&=0
\end{align*}
Now, solve by setting each factor equal to zero and solve. \begin{align*}
(x+3)(x+7)&=0\\
\Rightarrow \hspace{0.2cm}(x+3)=0 \hspace{0.3cm} \text{or} \hspace{0.3cm} (x+7)&=0\\
\Rightarrow \hspace{0.2cm} x&=-3 \hspace{0.3cm} \text{or} \hspace{0.3cm} x&=-7
\end{align*}
